            "explain": "$S$ has $\\binom{k}{2}$ edges; the probability they all match a chosen colour is $2^{-\\binom{k}{2}}$, and there are $2$ colour choices. So $\\mathbb{P}(S\\text{ monochromatic}) = 2 \\cdot 2^{-\\binom{k}{2}} = 2^{1-\\binom{k}{2}}$."
